x4freetext: Measurement of the fast-neutron fission cross sections
Detection efficiency 92% for Pa-231, 98% for Am-243,
Detector for alphas at nuclei ratio measurement
Even this Entry is marked as approved by the author,
it looks like EN-RSL-FW -> EN-RSL-HW - see plotted
SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
to REL-REF. Refs on Engl.transl. added. Title and list
M.M. Previous correction of SD was
checked at CJD. Corrections of data in Subent 003.
EN-RSL -> EN-RSL-FW in Subents 004-006 - see also
the added COMMENT. REL-REFs were corrected .
Minor correction of free text in STATUS in all Subents.
Oxide films of protactinium and plutonium on platinum
foils. Diameter 15 mm. Pa-231 content is 100%,
Pu-239 content is 99.891%, Pu-240 content is .109%
Correction were made on neutron difference in fissi-
onable layers (1.4% at 2.5 MeV),on fission chamber
energy dependence (0.8% at 2.5 MeV), on experimental
hall background (0.7% at 2.5 MeV), on target neutron
scattering (0.6% at 2.5 MeV), on associated particles
